name: AnnotationTypeMismatchException
comment:
Thrown to indicate that a program has attempted to access an element of
 an annotation whose type has changed after the annotation was compiled
 (or serialized).
 This exception can be thrown by the {@linkplain
 java.lang.reflect.AnnotatedElement API used to read annotations
 reflectively}.

constructors.name: AnnotationTypeMismatchException
constructors.comment:
Constructs an AnnotationTypeMismatchException for the specified
 annotation type element and found data type.

methods.name: element
methods.comment: Returns the <tt>Method</tt> object for the incorrectly typed element.

methods.name: foundType
methods.comment:
Returns the type of data found in the incorrectly typed element.
 The returned string may, but is not required to, contain the value
 as well.  The exact format of the string is unspecified.
